parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks when shifting gears
the vehicle accelerates slowly
and the engine RPMs fluctuate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ECM failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences harsh shifting
slipping
or jerking when shifting gears
and the engine RPMs fluctuate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the driver is attempting to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage gears
or the vehicle experiences complete loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when shifting gears, making it difficult to accelerate or merge into traffic, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine revs but does not move forward
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window system can cause the window to malfunction, which can lead to distraction or loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The power window does not stay closed
the window moves up and down on its own
the window gets stuck in an open or closed position
the window makes a strange noise when operating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, which can lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while in cruise control
the vehicle does not respond to cruise control inputs
the cruise control system malfunctions or fails to disengage.
